Defendant in custody.  
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of ten (10) years.  Five (5) years initial confinement, followed by five (5) years extended supervision.  As conditions of extended supervision:
1) Maintain absolute sobriety;
2) No entry into any establishment whose primary purpose is the sale of alcohol;
3) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling/job search combination;
5) Defendant is to keep a picture of the victim in his cell if it is provided by his family and with their approval;
6) When on extended supervision, perform forty (40) hours of community service per year by speaking to victim impact panels or school groups regarding the impact this has had on his life and his families life.
7) Every year while on extended supervision on 02-16-15 he is to visit the gravesite of the victim with the consent of the victim's family;
8) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
9) Pay costs of action;
10) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
11) Provide DNA sample;
12) Pay restitution of $6,459.76 to the victim's family and hold open the matter for an additional counseling bills.
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant is given credit for 87 days already served.  
$6,000.00 cash bail from 14 CF 78 and 14 CF 458 is to be applied to restitution to Larry & Patricia Waterman, 503 Jackson Street, P.O. Box 6, Mishicot, WI  54228.
